OL,6,F"Gale forced his way into the property
OL,7,Fand knocked his victim to the ground.
OL,8,FHe then forced her upstairs where she
OL,9,Ffeared there may be a sexual assault
OL,10,Fand demanded that she hand over
OL,11,Fjewellery and money.
OL,13,F"He left with four gold chains which
OL,14,Fhave sadly never been recovered.
OL,16,F"Burglary is an offence that greatly
OL,17,Faffects our communities and can be
OL,18,Fextremely distressing for victims, and
OL,19,FI am pleased that Gale has been
OL,20,Fbrought to justice so the victim can
OL,21,Fnow have closure.
